 -= Shutdown =-  (Admin Command)

 Usage:  shutdown [-t <minutes> | -c] <str>

 Examples:

    shutdown reason
    shutdown -t 5 reason
    shutdown -c

 This command can be used by admins to restart the mud, for the specified reason.  The -t flag will begin a timed shutdown, using the specified number of minutes.  The -c flag will cancel a timed shutdown.